<h2><a name="putc" id="putc">putc</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Syntax:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cstdio&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">int</span> putc<span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">int</span> ch<span class="sy0">,</span> FILE <span class="sy0">*</span>stream <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;</pre>
<p>

The putc() function writes the character ch to stream. The return value is the
character written, or <acronym title="End of file">EOF</acronym> if there is an error. For example:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">     <span class="kw4">int</span> ch;
     FILE <span class="sy0">*</span>input<span class="sy0">,</span> <span class="sy0">*</span>output;
     input <span class="sy0">=</span> fopen<span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="st0">&quot;tmp.c&quot;</span><span class="sy0">,</span> <span class="st0">&quot;r&quot;</span> <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;
     output <span class="sy0">=</span> fopen<span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="st0">&quot;tmpCopy.c&quot;</span><span class="sy0">,</span> <span class="st0">&quot;w&quot;</span> <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;
     ch <span class="sy0">=</span> getc<span class="br0">&#40;</span> input <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;
     <span class="kw1">while</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> ch <span class="sy0">!=</span> EOF <span class="br0">&#41;</span> <span class="br0">&#123;</span>
       putc<span class="br0">&#40;</span> ch<span class="sy0">,</span> output <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;
       ch <span class="sy0">=</span> getc<span class="br0">&#40;</span> input <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;
     <span class="br0">&#125;</span>
     fclose<span class="br0">&#40;</span> input <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;
     fclose<span class="br0">&#40;</span> output <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;</pre>
<p>

generates a copy of the file tmp.c called tmpCopy.c.
</p>

